There’s a lot to love here; gorgeous screenplay and a stunning final score from Sakamoto.

Visually, this is on par with Spirited Away as the most stunning Ghibli production ever released. It really feels like Miyazaki pulled out all the stops; at times dark and aggressive like Mononoke and at others light and playful like Ponyo. It’s delicious. Yet when it comes to the story, I felt really disappointed by Mahito.
